      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t see why setting $HOME is necessary here. It should be getting passed automatically from the environment, right?\n\nIs this code called during an emerge, because that would explain it. Every ebuild sets $HOME to a directory inside its work area. This would make the go cache useless since there would be a new one for every emerge and it would get wiped after the emerge is done.\n\nMaybe you should set $GOCACHE to explicitly point to a directory to use for the build cache.",
      "revId": "4493c8196d28d695a1afbbaf49c01f613a854514",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "66130302_726c5e01",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/build/build.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 73,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000042
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-25T22:44:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this code is executed by the tast command when a developer wants to rebuild and execute tests as described at https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromiumos/platform/tast/+/HEAD/docs/running_tests.md#Controlling-whether-tests-are-rebuilt.\n\nexec.Cmd starts out with an empty environment, as far as i\u0027m aware -- that\u0027s why i\u0027m copying over HOME from the current environment. i could copy all of os.Environ to it, but it seems safer to only set the vars that i need to use here.\n\ncopying over GOCACHE in case the user has set it to something else makes sense, though -- i\u0027ll do that.",
      "parentUuid": "8a393c55_6e239560",
      "revId": "4493c8196d28d695a1afbbaf49c01f613a854514",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3c799b87_5ee393af",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/build/build.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 73,
