      "writtenOn": "2018-04-25T23:21:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see. Looking at the canonical example for exec.Command: https://golang.org/pkg/os/exec/#Command\n\nIt would be cleaner to write:\n\ncmd.Env \u003d append(os.Environ(),\n        \"GOPATH\u003d\" + strings.Join([]string{cfg.TestWorkspace, cfg.CommonWorkspace, cfg.SysGopath}, \":\"),\n        \"GOBIN\u003d\" + outDir,\n)\n\nThose two look like the only two variables you need to override, with everything else coming from the environment.",
      "parentUuid": "66130302_726c5e01",
      "revId": "4493c8196d28d695a1afbbaf49c01f613a854514",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a686c70f_3f711e77",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/cmd/tast/build/build.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 73,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000042
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-25T23:28:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "there are various other GO___ variables (GOOS, GOARCH, GOROOT, etc.). i think that starting with a clean environment is safer than hoping that the user hasn\u0027t set anything that will mess up what this command is trying to do.",
      "parentUuid": "3c799b87_5ee393af",
      "revId": "4493c8196d28d695a1afbbaf49c01f613a854514",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
